<br>
Anyway, the best way to kill the Queen (from all accounts I've read, and collaborated by how it went down both times we killed her Sunday), is full-out offensive from the get-go. As someone already mentioned, if you have time to mana sieve her, she's been alive too long. Melees need to use their best offensive discs, casters need to nuke the crap out of her from the start. The more seconds she's alive the more chance she has to nail the entire raid with that unresistable (ok, maybe resistable with 400+ FR, can't confirm that) 2000 point AE. (I think it's 2000, that's what the top of my head is telling me; in any case, it's nasty.) She doesn't have a whole lot of hp, only around 10k, so she goes down quick if everyone goes nuts on her. Clerics should have group heals memmed. The shamans on Sunday were saying that they had a couple spells that could cure the dot too but I can't remember what they were. Blood of Nadox and something else?<br>
<br>
We fought her in the King room and she didn't have time to gate. I can't remember if she even tried to cast it. But pushing her around should work (it works to keep Vox from CHing herself too), or pulling her room clean and then charging her is also supposed to be a valid tactic from what I've read. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=valkyriebuffinstuff@firionavie>Valkyrie Buffinstuff</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 52<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(5/22/03 5:52 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm59.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=569.topic&index=42>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> k</span><hr size=1> Blood of Nadox/Pureblood are the spells that allegedly cure the queen's DoT.  I can't confirm this as I haven't got the darn spell yet -- slacker shaman!<br>
<br>
Anyway, as to the resistability of the queen's AE, I DID resist her twice with FR ~200 last time; that was how I was the last one standing, for all the good THAT did.  Of course, being level 61 may have something to do with that.  The second-to-last person up was a ranjor who was standing oor, trying to use Trueshot (unfortunately he had no LOS after we pushed her around the corner).<br>
<br>
My suggestions are thus:  <br>
<br>
Any shaman planning to come have Blood of Nadox just for shits and giggles, maybe it works.  <br>
<br>
Try to bring a 60+ cleric next time; Aego really does make a difference, especially on the nukers.<br>
<br>
Be a bit more strict on buff order since we're dealing with dispels.  I know, I know, &quot;dispel is random!&quot; but the first buff ALWAYS gets stripped.  If this is a HP or important resist buff, things get ugly quick.<br>
<br>
Pick a corner and push her into it, OR push her down the hall toward the library so we don't have LOS issues for the casters and rangers.  Maybe some of them can stay oor a little longer this way.  Alternatively, fight her in the King's room after it's cleared.<br>
<br>
Um, I have a few others but I'm late for work!  Ciao!!<br>
<br>
Valkyrie<br>
61 Oracle<br>
