 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=blinkun12>Blinkun12</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 14<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(5/23/03 11:07 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm59.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=569.topic&index=43>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: k</span><hr size=1> Chanters have 3 mana sieving spells that do any amount worth mentioning.  They are also incredibly hard to resist.<br>
<br>
The main problem with them is their recast time.  Mana sieve which is basically a DD against mana has a recast time of 8 seconds.  It reduces mana by 370 at level 60.  It is unresistable which is very very good.<br>
<br>
Theft of thought is a mana tap.  It steals mana from the target and gives it to the caster.  It does 400 mana and has a recast of 2 minutes.<br>
<br>
Scryer's Trespass is a mana tap over time.  It does 50 mana a tick for 10 ticks.  So 500 mana total.  It has a recast of 3 minutes 20 seconds.<br>
<br>
So a chanter can<br>
<br>
mana sieve, <br>
scryer's trespass,<br>
mana sieve, <br>
theft of though, <br>
mana sieve <br>
<br>
in order for the fastest mana drain possible.  It will do 1830 mana damage in 30 seconds.  In the next 30 seconds you can mana sieve almost 3 more times bringing the grand total once scryer's has done its full weight of mana tapping to almost 3000 mana in 1 minute.<br>
<br>
The whole time the chanter is regaining mana from Scryer's and TofT so he/she can continue to cast these spells as they are available.<br>
<br>
Being the only high end enchanter in my guild it was my sole responsibility to keep the giants in the Kael Arena from gating when they were low and I had absolutely no problem doing this myself.  Caster MOBs will expend all but the last bit of mana they have during a fight.  Leaving enough for gate or a Complete heal or two.  1 enchanter can easily drain this last bit of mana.<br>
<br>
So to make a long story short.  That Queen is gonna die if you have a dedicated mana tapper or two. <p><br>
